Two police officers were gunned down in Bloekombos outside Cape Town this morning and a manhunt for the killers is under way. SAPS spokesperson Andre Traut earlier spoke to eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Two suspects in the murder of two police officers in Cape Town have been arrested.
The officers were gunned down in the early hours of Sunday morning while patrolling in Bloekombos. READ: Two police officers killed in Western Cape The victims were a 46-year-old sergeant and a 28-year-old constable. They were shot while still inside their police car. The suspects stole the officers' guns before running away. The Hawks have taken over the investigation of the murders, which are being strongly condemned by National Police Commissioner, Khehla Sitole.